<p>The concept of the &ldquo;FullAutoCAM&rdquo; command is to create high-quality machining data quickly regardless of operator skills.<br>The command consists of a set of functions to streamline all types of CAM operations in the phases from that of process designing to that of creating NC data.</p><p align="center"><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://www.biprogy-uel.co.jp/cadmeister/e/function/cam/eimages/full_auto_cam_01_2022.jpg" alt="" width="780" height="435" class="fr-fic fr-dii"><br><br></p><p>The Company will continue research and deliberations with the aim of further improving the automatic functions of the &ldquo;FullAutoCAM&rdquo; command and expand areas<br>where the command is accepted. We will strengthen the functions conducive to shortening CAM operation time and stabilizing machining quality.</p><p><br></p><h2 class="fr-text-bordered">Feature</h2><h3>Automatic Machining Design</h3><hr><p>Execute the &ldquo;ShapeMachining&rdquo; command and the &ldquo;ProfileMachining&rdquo; command in coordination with the &ldquo;AutomaticMachiningDesign&rdquo; command in order to enable the System<br>to read data of machining-subject shape surfaces and lines in the command window of the &ldquo;AutomaticMachiningDesign&rdquo; command and automatically decide an optimum process sequence.<br>Execute the &ldquo;AutomaticMachiningDesign&rdquo; command in coordination with the command of automatically choosing cutting tools of no interference in order to enable the System to automatically create cutting paths that cause no interference.<br><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://www.biprogy-uel.co.jp/cadmeister/e/function/cam/eimages/full_auto_cam_02_2022.jpg" alt="自動加工設計" width="780" height="211" class="fr-fic fr-dii"><br></p><p><br></p><h3>Automatically Optimize Machining Sequences</h3><hr><p>The &ldquo;AutomaticallyOptimizeMachiningSequences&rdquo; command enables the System to automatically realign cutting paths created by the &ldquo;Shape Machining&rdquo; command and the &ldquo;Profile Machining&rdquo; command in compliance with rules based upon considerations about actual cutting sequences.<br>The function of Cutting Tools Life Division of the &ldquo;AutomaticallyOptimizeMachiningSequences&rdquo; command enables the System operators to replace cutting tools of use in units of cutting length and time.<br>The &ldquo;AutomaticallyOptimizeMachiningSequences&rdquo; command enables the System operators to optimize motions of a tool cutting along paths of different heights in concurrence with replacing cutting tools.<br><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://www.biprogy-uel.co.jp/cadmeister/e/function/cam/eimages/full_auto_cam_03_2022.jpg" alt="加工順の自動最適化1" width="780" height="168" class="fr-fic fr-dii"><br><br><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://www.biprogy-uel.co.jp/cadmeister/e/function/cam/eimages/full_auto_cam_04_2022.jpg" alt="加工順の自動最適化2" width="427" height="86" class="fr-fic fr-dii"><br></p><p><br></p><h3>Standardize Databases</h3><hr><p>Store decive factors for finalizing process sequences as expertize in a database. The System will automatically decide process sequences on the basis of the database, regardless of operator skills.<br><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://www.biprogy-uel.co.jp/cadmeister/e/function/cam/eimages/full_auto_cam_05_2022.jpg" alt="データベース標準化" width="780" height="432" class="fr-fic fr-dii"><br><br></p><h3>&nbsp;Inquiries</h3><p>If you have any inquiries about our product or would like to request a visit to your place for explanation or demonstration, please use the inquiry form.</p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>